# Python Version Rule

- Project Python version is fixed to `3.11`.
- Create virtual environments with `python3.11 -m venv venv`.
- In deployment or startup scripts, avoid ambiguous interpreters (`python` / `python3`) when version matters.
- If an existing virtual environment is not Python `3.11`, recreate it before installing dependencies.

```bash
# BAD
python3 -m venv venv

# GOOD
python3.11 -m venv venv
```
